      "writtenOn": "2019-06-18T13:31:00Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "I had not realized that the makeTextureImage() used the resource cache to preserve the mapping from image unique id to texture, so I was concerned that if I always called makeTextureImage() in onDraw(), then it would always upload the texture each frame. But on closer look, that appears not to be the case, so I will switch these to just be sk_sp\u003cSkImage\u003e holding the original data, and then call makeTextureImage() in onDraw().\n\nThis also means I can remove the unnecessary AutoGPUImage type that I added to achieve the same end of not re-uploading image data.",
